This avoids the mutex deadlock because `ensure_run_started()` is called outside the lock. When `ensure_run_started()` calls `record()` (inner), the inner `record()` acquires the lock, writes RunStarted, releases the lock. Then the outer `record()` acquires the lock and writes its event.

